definition: Goh Chok Tong (1941-), Singapore businessman and politician, prime minister 1990-2004

sentences.english: Goh Chok Tong said, China's development has brought new opportunities to Asia and the world, and the two countries have broad prospects for future cooperation.
sentences.chinese: 吳作棟表示，中國的發展給亞洲和世界帶來新的機遇。

sentences.english: When did Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong first enter the political arena?
sentences.chinese: 吳作棟哪一年第一次進入政治舞臺？

sentences.english: The Chinese premier is visiting Singapore at the invitation of Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong.
sentences.chinese: 中國總理在吳作棟總理的邀請下訪問新加坡。
